Bumps [fixed](https://gitlab.com/tspiteri/fixed) from 1.21.0 to 1.22.1.
Changelog

Sourced from fixed's changelog.

Version 1.22.1 (2023-01-26)

  • The errors from the lit method have been improved.
  • The track_caller attribute is now applied to many more inline functions that can panic.

Version 1.22.0 (2023-01-25)

  • String parsing now supports an optional exponent for all supported radices.
  • The lit method was added to all fixed-point numbers. This is useful to write fixed-point numbers literally in code and also works in constant context.
  • All fixed-point numbers now implement [LowerExp] and [UpperExp].
  • The Fixed and FixedBits traits now have the added supertraits [Binary], [Octal], [LowerHex], [UpperHex], [LowerExp] and [UpperExp].
  • The Wrapping and Unwrapped wrappers now implement [Binary], [Octal], [LowerHex], [UpperHex], [LowerExp] and [UpperExp].
  • The implementation of [Debug] for fixed-point numbers now has more relaxed constraints on the fractional bits generic parameter: now Frac only needs to implement Unsigned.

  • 19cc9b2 move some identifiers into format strings
  • 26ac562 add some ParseErrorKind variants
  • ad96700 style

title: `integration_tests`: don't panic in panic handler
body:
The `Drop` implementation on `integration_tests::janus::Janus` tries to copy logs out of interop test containers using `docker cp`. It would panic if that failed, which would result in a double panic (because test failures in `cargo test` are panics), and that would cause output from failing tests to be lost, making it hard to diagnose failures.

With this change, we no longer panic if either we can't `exec(2)` `docker` or if `docker cp` fails. Instead, the errors get printed to stdout so at least they will appear in GitHub Actions logs, as will some information about the test that failed.

Example test failure _without_ this change:
https://github.com/divviup/janus/actions/runs/4010819099/jobs/6887739020

Example test failure _with_ this change:
https://github.com/divviup/janus/actions/runs/4011174836/jobs/6888472737

- aggregator

  - upload
  - aggregate_init
  - aggregate_continue
  - collect
  - aggregate_share
  - get_collect_job_get_task
  - get_collect_job
  - delete_collect_job_get_task

- aggregation job creator
  - aggregation_job_creator_get_tasks
  - aggregation_job_creator_time_with_param
  - aggregation_job_creator_fixed_no_param
  - aggregation_job_creator_time_no_param
- aggregation_job_driver
  - step_aggregation_job_2
  - step_aggregation_job_1
  - cancel_aggregation_job
  - acquire_aggregation_jobs
- collect_job_driver
  - step_collect_job_2
  - step_collect_job_1
  - abandon_collect_job
  - acquire_collect_jobs

Future work: this would enable adding a histogram metric to record the elapsed time in transactions. (without a transaction name label, heterogeneity would make such a histogram hard to interpret)

title: Reject uploaded reports past expiry age (0.2)
body: This is a follow-up to #894, changing `/upload` to reject reports with `...:reportTooLate` if the given task has a report expiry age configured, and the report is older than that age. We need to check for this because otherwise an attacker could re-upload the same report multiple times once it's old enough to be garbage collected, and race collections against the garbage collector to get around anti-replay protections.

title: Miscellaneous query type-related cleanups
body:
I reviewed the codebase to check that we have parity between the two query types, and I came up with three small cleanups to make.

- `/aggregate` was broken for fixed size queries with the dummy VDAF.
- `test_task_builders()` can be slightly simplified now that `TaskBuilder::new()` takes the query type.
- `dap_decode` would have output an extra `Ok(...)` around one particular message type.

title: Fix flaky test by changing number of retries - 0.2 backport
body: This is a backport of #916 to the 0.2 release branch.

title: Fix flaky test by changing number of retries
body: Mocked responses for two APIs in this test previously returned three errors before returning a successful response. On rare occasions, the 10ms maximum elapsed time limit from `test_http_request_exponential_backoff()` would be exceeded on the third error, and the test would fail. This PR changes the mocks to only return one error before succeeding, which should give us plenty of buffer.

title: replace `generate_vdaf_values` with `run_vdaf`
body:
The tests in mod `datastore` defined a mechanism for running a VDAF and recording a transcript, which is redundant given `run_vdaf` and `VdafTranscript` in `janus_core`. This commit moves `datastore` tests to `run_vdaf`. Additionally, `VdafTranscript` now has convenience methods for getting preparation state and output shares, which absolves its clients of writing gnarly `assert_matches!` macros that get so long that `rustfmt` gives up on tidying them up.

---

I'm working on the changes needed to implement DAP-04 in https://github.com/divviup/janus/pull/731. Since DAP-04 isn't ready yet and in order to reduce the size of the eventual PR wiring up the new HTTP API, I'm teasing out some independent pieces into more digestible PRs.

title: integrating bounded l2 norm fixed point vector sum types.
body:
As discussed [here](https://github.com/divviup/janus/issues/464), this PR enables using our [prio3 type for aggregating vectors of fixed-point numbers](https://github.com/divviup/libprio-rs/pull/283) with janus. It mainly adds the enum cases and match branches required to dispatch on the 16-, 32- and 64-bit variants of fixed-point vector aggregation.

One notable thing I did is adding a [helper enum to enable tagging the JSON from the upload request with the fixedpoint type in the end-to-end interop test](https://github.com/dpsa-project/janus/blob/abda6a06637014808cdfead37912d88b2ca972bb/interop_binaries/src/bin/janus_interop_client.rs#L30-L43) only for our vectors, as the standard string representation of fixedpoint numbers does not carry that information.

Looking forward to your comments :)
